cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with game theory and auction mechanisms, which are commonly studied in the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of agents and the modeling of their failures suggests a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The analysis of equilibrium and strategy also suggests a connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The examination of various methods of influencing participation suggests a connection to the cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the use of mathematical modeling and characterization of equilibrium suggests a connection to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
